"{\"uid\": \"awfulannouncing.com-tech-nbc-olympics-heart-rate-monitors.html\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Awful Announcing  NBC is adding a wholly unnecessary, yet somewhat interesting, tweak to some of their Summer Olympics coverage.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 128, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 18, \"end\": 21, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\", \"score\": 0.9999658411211254, \"rank\": 3.355537836975613e-05, \"text\": \"NBC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In a lengthy feature about this summer's games from Paris,Varietyreveals that NBC is outfitting the parents of athletes competing with heart rate monitors and will display the results on-screen.\", \"from\": 130, \"to\": 324, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 182, \"end\": 187, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999989999812895, \"rank\": 1.000019607937407e-06, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 208, \"end\": 211, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\", \"score\": 0.9999658411211254, \"rank\": 3.355537836975613e-05, \"text\": \"NBC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In something that might seem more at home on \\\"America's Got Talent\\\" or \\\"The Voice,\\\" the network even plans to deploy five heart-\\u00adrate monitors among the parents of athletes.\", \"from\": 326, \"to\": 499, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The results will be shown on\\u00adscreen as moms and dads watch their kids compete - something that test audiences have loved.\", \"from\": 500, \"to\": 621, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Will the medical devices have an on-screen sponsor?\", \"from\": 622, \"to\": 673, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We are talking about it.\\\"\", \"from\": 674, \"to\": 700, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"says Dan Lovinger, the NBC ad-sales executive who is responsible for snaring hundreds of millions in ad support.\", \"from\": 701, \"to\": 813, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 724, \"end\": 727, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\", \"score\": 0.9999658411211254, \"rank\": 3.355537836975613e-05, \"text\": \"NBC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Adding the on-screen heart rate monitors is the latest addition to NBC's coverage, which is getting something of a makeover this summer.\", \"from\": 815, \"to\": 951, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 882, \"end\": 885, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\", \"score\": 0.9999658411211254, \"rank\": 3.355537836975613e-05, \"text\": \"NBC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Mike Tiricowill cohostthe Opening Ceremony alongside Kelly Clarkson and Peyton Manning, while the Closing Ceremonywill be cohostedby Tirico, Jimmy Fallon, Tara Lipinski, and Johnny Weir.Additionally, podcaster Alex Cooper will host watch parties on Peacock during various events and Snoop Doggwill returnas part of NBC's primetime coverage.\", \"from\": 953, \"to\": 1293, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1006, \"end\": 1020, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kelly_Clarkson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kelly Clarkson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kelly_Clarkson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kelly_Clarkson\"}, {\"begin\": 1025, \"end\": 1039, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peyton_Manning\", \"score\": 1.0, \